Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deletePinFromPinGroup(25.10)                      deletePinFromPinGroup(25.10)

Name
       deletePinFromPinGroup - Removes a port from a specified pin group

Syntax
       deletePinFromPinGroup

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>

       -pin {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}

       Removes a port from a specified pin group.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the module. The module name is not re-
              quired if the command is run on a top-level module.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deletePinFromPinGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deletePinFromPinGroup

       -pinGroup <pinGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the pin group that was created.

              Data_type: string, required

       -pin {<pinName> | <pinNameList>}
              Specifies the name(s) of the port(s) of the module.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command removes ports RASN1 and RASN2 of module SH17 from
       pin group pin17:

       deletePinFromPinGroup -cell SH17 -pinGroup pin17 -pin {RASN1 RASN2}

